SB004710.100 - 984 - XXXX 2/19/2026 11:42 AM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 47/GA
1 judge and shall promptly refer the employee to a duly qualified
2 "B" reader physician who is licensed in the Commonwealth and is
3 a board-certified pulmonary specialist as set forth pursuant to KRS
4 342.315 and 342.794(1). The report from this examination shall be
5 provided to all parties of record. The employee shall not be
6 referred by the commissioner for examination within two (2) years
7 following any prior referral for examination for the same disease.
8 c. The commissioner shall develop a procedure to annually audit the
9 performance of physicians and facilities that are selected to
10 perform examinations pursuant to this section. The audit shall
11 include an evaluation of the physician and facility with respect to
12 the timeliness and completeness of the reports and the frequency at
13 which the physician's classification of an X-ray differs from those
14 of the other physicians of that X-ray. The commissioner shall
15 remove a physician or facility from selection consideration if the
16 physician or facility consistently renders incomplete or untimely
17 reports or if the physician's interpretations of X-rays are not in
18 conformity with the readings of other physicians of record at least
19 fifty percent (50%) of the time. The report required under this
20 subdivision shall be provided to the Interim Joint Committee on
21 Economic Development and Workforce Investment on or before
22 July 1, 2019, and on or before July 1 of each year thereafter.
23 d. In coal workers' pneumoconiosis claims, if the physician selected
24 by the commissioner interprets an X-ray as positive for
25 complicated coal workers' pneumoconiosis, the commissioner
26 shall refer the employee to the facility at which the claimant was
27 previously evaluated for a computerized tomography scan in order
