1 the last injurious exposure to the occupational hazard.
2 (b) Income benefits for the disease of pneumoconiosis resulting from exposure to
3 coal dust or death therefrom shall not be payable unless the employee has
4 been exposed to the hazards of such pneumoconiosis in the Commonwealth of
5 Kentucky over a continuous period of not less than two (2) years during the
6 ten (10) years immediately preceding the date of his or her last exposure to
7 such hazard, or for any five (5) of the fifteen (15) years immediately
8 preceding the date of such last exposure.
9 (5) The amount of compensation payable for disability due to occupational disease or
10 for death from the disease, and the time and manner of its payment, shall be as
11 provided for under the general provisions of the Workers' Compensation Act, but:
12 (a) In no event shall the payment exceed the amounts that were in effect at the
