14 (b) The time of the beginning of compensation payments shall be the date of the
15 employee's last injurious exposure to the cause of the disease, or the date of
16 actual disability, whichever is later; and
17 (c) In case of death where the employee has been awarded compensation or made
18 timely claim within the period provided for in this section, and an employee
19 has suffered continuous disability to the date of his or her death occurring at
20 any time within twenty (20) years from the date of disability, his or her
21 dependents, if any, shall be awarded compensation for his or her death as
22 provided for under the general provisions of the Workers' Compensation Act
23 and in this section, except as provided in KRS 342.750(6).
24 (6) If an autopsy has been performed, no testimony relative thereto shall be admitted
25 unless the employer or its representative has available findings and reports of the
26 pathologist or doctor who performed the autopsy examination.
27 (7) No compensation shall be payable for occupational disease if the employee at the
