18 (12) A concluded claim for benefits by reason of contraction of coal workers'
19 pneumoconiosis in the severance or processing of coal shall bar any subsequent
20 claim for benefits by reason of contraction of coal workers' pneumoconiosis, unless
21 there has occurred in the interim between the conclusion of the first claim and the
22 filing of the second claim at least two (2) years of employment wherein the
23 employee was continuously exposed to the hazards of the disease in the
24 Commonwealth.
